1
00:00:00,917 --> 00:00:03,002
[Edward] <i>Alice,</i>
<i>don't look at me like that.</i>

2
00:00:03,086 --> 00:00:05,088
<i>You know that you're special to me.</i>

3
00:00:05,171 --> 00:00:06,506
<i>You are my favorite.</i>

4
00:00:08,383 --> 00:00:10,218
<i>I was traumatized for years!</i>

5
00:00:10,301 --> 00:00:11,803
<i>I thought I was going insane!</i>

6
00:00:11,886 --> 00:00:13,054
<i>I tried to change.</i>

7
00:00:13,138 --> 00:00:15,390
<i>But in the end,</i>
<i>I still couldn't control myself.</i>

8
00:00:15,473 --> 00:00:16,683
<i>Edong's already in the area.</i>

9
00:00:16,766 --> 00:00:18,893
<i>But Lucas isn't</i>
<i>sure of his exact location.</i>

10
00:00:18,977 --> 00:00:19,853
[Locsin] <i>Copy.</i>

11
00:00:19,936 --> 00:00:21,604
<i>- Put that down!</i>
<i>- This isn't Edong!</i>

12
00:00:21,688 --> 00:00:23,148
- [men grunting]
- [blows landing]

13
00:00:23,231 --> 00:00:25,942
<i>- There's Edong!</i>
<i>- You nasty bastard!</i>

14
00:00:26,025 --> 00:00:27,235
- [flesh squelching]
- [groans]

15
00:00:27,318 --> 00:00:28,987
- [gunshots]
<i>- Hey!</i>

16
00:00:29,070 --> 00:00:31,322
<i>Mike found out what I did to you.</i>

17
00:00:31,406 --> 00:00:32,991
<i>That's why Mike suddenly died</i>

18
00:00:33,074 --> 00:00:36,244
<i>before he could even</i>
<i>expose my secrets to everyone!</i>

19
00:00:39,164 --> 00:00:45,920
[theme music playing]

20
00:01:54,614 --> 00:01:58,451
[uneasy music playing]

21
00:01:58,535 --> 00:02:00,954
[crying] What did you do to him?

22
00:02:04,457 --> 00:02:07,127
[sobbing, screaming]
What did you do to him?!

23
00:02:09,212 --> 00:02:10,630
[music fades]

24
00:02:10,713 --> 00:02:12,882
[vendor] <i>Oh? Where's Susan?</i>

25
00:02:12,966 --> 00:02:14,759
<i>Looks like you're on shopping duty.</i>

26
00:02:14,843 --> 00:02:17,804
<i>She went out with Alice</i>
<i>today so she asked me instead.</i>

27
00:02:17,887 --> 00:02:19,055
[vendor] <i>Oh, I see.</i>

28
00:02:23,226 --> 00:02:24,477
<i>Sad, isn't it?</i>

29
00:02:25,562 --> 00:02:28,273
<i>Their daughter's been</i>
<i>missing for almost a decade now.</i>

30
00:02:28,731 --> 00:02:30,525
<i>They still haven't given up.</i>

31
00:02:35,238 --> 00:02:36,489
<i>Uh, sir?</i>

32
00:02:37,240 --> 00:02:40,535
<i>Sir, do you have</i>
<i>information about our daughter?</i>

33
00:02:41,077 --> 00:02:43,580
<i>Alright, we'll pray for you.</i>

34
00:02:44,205 --> 00:02:46,416
<i>Thank you. Come on.</i>

35
00:02:47,584 --> 00:02:49,627
<i>Aren't you Edward's cousin?</i>

36
00:02:50,003 --> 00:02:51,838
<i>Uh, yes. Yes, I am.</i>

37
00:02:51,921 --> 00:02:54,007
[crying] <i>You know, he was nice to Ella.</i>

38
00:02:54,799 --> 00:02:58,428
<i>My daughter loved</i>
<i>the lollipops he always gave her.</i>

39
00:02:59,178 --> 00:03:01,431
- [woman sighs]
- [stuttering] <i>Y-- you know Edward?</i>

40
00:03:01,973 --> 00:03:04,392
<i>He's a regular at our eatery.</i>

41
00:03:05,184 --> 00:03:07,020
<i>Send him our regards.</i>

42
00:03:07,395 --> 00:03:08,688
[man] <i>Thank you again, sir.</i>

43
00:03:08,771 --> 00:03:11,816
[foreboding music playing]

44
00:03:14,652 --> 00:03:15,945
[music fades]

45
00:03:16,029 --> 00:03:22,160
[utensils clinking]

46
00:03:25,872 --> 00:03:28,374
<i>The parents of the kid</i>
<i>were outside the church earlier.</i>

47
00:03:29,667 --> 00:03:31,544
<i>Handing out fliers.</i>

48
00:03:31,628 --> 00:03:32,670
<i>Do you know them?</i>

49
00:03:33,838 --> 00:03:36,341
<i>No. I just know that they own an eatery.</i>

50
00:03:37,467 --> 00:03:39,969
<i>Had we been too</i>
<i>late to find Alice back then,</i>

51
00:03:40,720 --> 00:03:44,057
<i>we would be going through</i>
<i>the same thing now.</i>

52
00:03:44,390 --> 00:03:46,017
[scoffs] <i>But she was found.</i>

53
00:03:46,100 --> 00:03:48,645
<i>And she's doing okay.</i>
<i>Think about that instead, Cous.</i>

54
00:03:49,604 --> 00:03:52,065
[ominous music sting]

55
00:03:55,235 --> 00:03:57,195
<i>Oh right, Cous, I forgot to mention.</i>

56
00:03:57,946 --> 00:04:00,865
<i>I saw Ella's parents at</i>
<i>the market this morning.</i>

57
00:04:03,243 --> 00:04:04,035
<i>Who?</i>

58
00:04:04,494 --> 00:04:05,662
<i>Uh… Ella.</i>

59
00:04:06,079 --> 00:04:08,456
<i>The missing kid before. It's been years.</i>

60
00:04:09,374 --> 00:04:13,878
<i>Oh… I never saw the kid before</i>
<i>but apparently she was Alice's age?</i>

61
00:04:13,962 --> 00:04:15,004
<i>Right?</i>

62
00:04:16,965 --> 00:04:18,800
[woman] <i>You know, he's nice to Ella.</i>

63
00:04:19,300 --> 00:04:23,304
[crying] <i>She loved</i>
<i>the lollipops he always gave her.</i>

64
00:04:23,388 --> 00:04:24,931
[Mike] <i>You know Edward?</i>

65
00:04:25,682 --> 00:04:27,892
[woman] <i>He's a regular at our eatery.</i>

66
00:04:27,976 --> 00:04:30,311
[unsettling music playing]

67
00:04:30,395 --> 00:04:32,897
<i>Hey, don't fart just yet.</i>

68
00:04:32,981 --> 00:04:34,565
<i>Let me get to a safe distance first!</i>

69
00:04:34,649 --> 00:04:36,734
- [Mike scoffs]
- [Edward laughing]

70
00:04:37,360 --> 00:04:40,154
[tools clinking]

71
00:04:40,238 --> 00:04:41,614
[music fades]

72
00:04:42,448 --> 00:04:44,450
[Susan] <i>There were so many people earlier!</i>

73
00:04:44,826 --> 00:04:46,786
<i>I should have done the groceries sooner.</i>

74
00:04:47,745 --> 00:04:48,705
<i>Huh?</i>

75
00:04:48,788 --> 00:04:50,039
<i>Why did I buy this?</i>

76
00:04:51,082 --> 00:04:52,375
<i>Do you remember?</i>

77
00:04:53,376 --> 00:04:55,503
<i>This was Alice's favorite before.</i>

78
00:04:56,129 --> 00:04:59,549
<i>She asked for this almost every day,</i>
<i>we could never say no to her.</i>

79
00:05:00,091 --> 00:05:02,051
<i>And then…</i>
<i>all of a sudden she got sick of them.</i>

80
00:05:03,052 --> 00:05:08,558
[unsettling music resumes]

81
00:05:09,976 --> 00:05:14,022
[Mike] <i>Dear,</i>
<i>daddy's got something for you!</i>

82
00:05:14,647 --> 00:05:17,317
<i>Here! Ta-da!</i>

83
00:05:17,400 --> 00:05:18,818
<i>Isn't this your favorite?</i>

84
00:05:18,901 --> 00:05:20,570
[Mike] <i>Right? Right?</i>

85
00:05:20,653 --> 00:05:25,116
[eerie music playing]

86
00:05:30,330 --> 00:05:32,248
<i>I bought the right thing, didn't I?</i>

87
00:05:32,332 --> 00:05:33,750
<i>Isn't this your favorite?</i>

88
00:05:47,722 --> 00:05:52,894
[eerie music continues]

89
00:06:02,361 --> 00:06:03,905
[Edward] <i>Sure, I'll help you.</i>

90
00:06:08,868 --> 00:06:10,078
[Edward] <i>Alright then.</i>

91
00:06:11,662 --> 00:06:12,997
<i>Hello! </i>[chuckles]

92
00:06:13,081 --> 00:06:14,123
<i>Would you like a lollipop?</i>

93
00:06:14,707 --> 00:06:15,958
[plastic wrapper crinkling]

94
00:06:17,168 --> 00:06:20,379
[eerie music continues]

95
00:06:20,463 --> 00:06:22,423
- [girl] <i>Thank you!</i>
<i>- You're welcome.</i>

96
00:06:22,507 --> 00:06:23,382
[Edward chuckles]

97
00:06:24,258 --> 00:06:28,805
[eerie music continues]

98
00:06:35,186 --> 00:06:37,522
[woman] <i>You're Edward's cousin, right?</i>

99
00:06:37,605 --> 00:06:39,649
<i>You know, he's so nice towards Ella.</i>

100
00:06:40,233 --> 00:06:43,569
<i>She loved</i>
<i>the lollipops he always gave her.</i>

101
00:06:43,653 --> 00:06:49,200
[music becomes foreboding]

102
00:06:54,372 --> 00:06:56,207
<i>- Cousin!</i>
<i>- What did you do, huh?!</i>

103
00:06:56,290 --> 00:06:58,626
<i>What did you do to her?!</i>
<i>What did you do to Alice?!</i>

104
00:07:00,169 --> 00:07:02,505
<i>- What happened to Alice?</i>
<i>- What did you do to my child?!</i>

105
00:07:02,588 --> 00:07:03,673
[Christina] <i>Mike!</i>

106
00:07:03,756 --> 00:07:08,261
[foreboding music continues]

107
00:07:19,313 --> 00:07:25,111
[music turns sullen]

108
00:07:42,545 --> 00:07:44,005
[anguished scream]

109
00:07:53,264 --> 00:08:00,229
[sullen music continues]

110
00:08:03,149 --> 00:08:08,488
[crying]

111
00:08:08,571 --> 00:08:10,948
[Christina] <i>He didn't</i>
<i>even say what the problem was.</i>

112
00:08:11,032 --> 00:08:12,366
[music fades]

113
00:08:16,037 --> 00:08:17,205
<i>Heart.</i>

114
00:08:17,288 --> 00:08:19,207
<i>Don't worry about that anymore, okay?</i>

115
00:08:19,665 --> 00:08:21,000
<i>That's just cousin Mike.</i>

116
00:08:21,751 --> 00:08:24,420
<i>I'm sure we'll talk it through later.</i>

117
00:08:24,504 --> 00:08:25,671
[chuckles]

118
00:08:25,755 --> 00:08:27,507
<i>This is nothing. Hm?</i>

119
00:08:27,590 --> 00:08:32,303
[uneasy music playing]

120
00:08:38,476 --> 00:08:40,811
- [phone ringing]
- [Mike sniffles]

121
00:08:43,105 --> 00:08:44,607
[ringing continues]

122
00:08:45,483 --> 00:08:47,193
- [Mike sniffles] <i>Ha…</i>
- [phone ringing]

123
00:08:51,280 --> 00:08:52,740
<i>Uh, hello, my dear?</i>

124
00:08:53,699 --> 00:08:54,992
<i>Pa? Are you on the way home?</i>

125
00:08:56,536 --> 00:08:58,246
<i>Why? Is there a problem?</i>

126
00:08:58,746 --> 00:09:00,706
<i>Pa, come pick me up, please.</i>

127
00:09:02,041 --> 00:09:03,084
<i>Okay, all right.</i>

128
00:09:03,668 --> 00:09:06,087
<i>I'll come there,</i>
<i>I'll pick you up. Just wait for me.</i>

129
00:09:07,088 --> 00:09:09,465
<i>Okay. See you.</i>

130
00:09:09,549 --> 00:09:10,883
[exhales deeply]

131
00:09:15,137 --> 00:09:16,847
[uneasy music fades]

132
00:09:16,931 --> 00:09:19,976
[panicked breaths]

133
00:09:20,059 --> 00:09:23,062
What did you do to him?! What did you do?!

134
00:09:23,145 --> 00:09:25,022
- What did you do?!
- I didn't do anything to Mike!

135
00:09:25,106 --> 00:09:27,650
What happened was an accident!
Weren't you with him?!

136
00:09:27,733 --> 00:09:30,987
[crying]

137
00:09:31,070 --> 00:09:32,154
[young Alice] <i>Papa?</i>

138
00:09:34,115 --> 00:09:35,700
<i>Is there a problem with the engine?</i>

139
00:09:35,783 --> 00:09:38,119
<i>Ah</i>… <i>No, nothing's wrong, dear.</i>

140
00:09:38,202 --> 00:09:41,455
<i>Um, I just heard something thumping.</i>

141
00:09:41,956 --> 00:09:44,458
<i>I just checked, but nothing's wrong.</i>

142
00:09:44,959 --> 00:09:46,127
<i>Okay.</i>

143
00:09:46,794 --> 00:09:48,713
[tools clanging]

144
00:09:51,090 --> 00:09:53,426
[Mike] <i>Let's get back to our conversation.</i>

145
00:09:53,509 --> 00:09:55,678
<i>So, Louisa Soria…</i>

146
00:09:56,304 --> 00:09:58,014
<i>Her brother is Lester?</i>

147
00:09:59,098 --> 00:10:00,308
[young Alice sighs]

148
00:10:01,017 --> 00:10:03,519
<i>If that's the case</i>
<i>and her claim is true…</i>

149
00:10:04,395 --> 00:10:05,771
<i>That's a serious issue.</i>

150
00:10:06,314 --> 00:10:08,065
<i>She could report it to the police!</i>

151
00:10:08,149 --> 00:10:10,693
<i>But she didn't tell</i>
<i>it to the principal, Papa.</i>

152
00:10:12,820 --> 00:10:14,572
<i>She's probably scared, my dear.</i>

153
00:10:15,656 --> 00:10:18,284
<i>Especially that it's</i>
<i>Kyle Sebastian she's accusing.</i>

154
00:10:18,951 --> 00:10:23,664
<i>You know Kyle's family, right?</i>
<i>They're well-known in Amurao.</i>

155
00:10:23,748 --> 00:10:29,587
[pensive music playing]

156
00:10:34,592 --> 00:10:36,802
[tires screeching]

157
00:10:37,637 --> 00:10:39,055
[handbrake creaking]

158
00:10:39,138 --> 00:10:41,932
[seatbelt clicks, thuds]

159
00:10:42,016 --> 00:10:44,935
[pensive music continues]

160
00:10:45,019 --> 00:10:46,312
<i>What about you, Alice?</i>

161
00:10:47,897 --> 00:10:49,190
<i>Are you sure…</i>

162
00:10:49,774 --> 00:10:51,567
<i>Kyle didn't do anything to you?</i>

163
00:10:52,818 --> 00:10:54,570
<i>I've just only interacted with him today.</i>

164
00:10:54,654 --> 00:10:59,575
[pensive music continues]

165
00:11:01,535 --> 00:11:02,578
<i>Um…</i>

166
00:11:03,454 --> 00:11:04,497
<i>Alice?</i>

167
00:11:06,165 --> 00:11:07,541
[music fades]

168
00:11:07,625 --> 00:11:08,542
<i>Um…</i>

169
00:11:12,296 --> 00:11:13,964
<i>Don't worry, okay?</i>

170
00:11:14,507 --> 00:11:16,759
<i>When we meet the principal tomorrow,</i>

171
00:11:17,551 --> 00:11:18,886
<i>we'll find out everything.</i>

172
00:11:19,804 --> 00:11:22,056
<i>- Don't worry.</i>
<i>- Thank you, Pa.</i>

173
00:11:22,765 --> 00:11:28,104
[melancholic music playing]

174
00:11:31,023 --> 00:11:33,192
<i>- Milkshake?</i>
- [music fades]

175
00:11:33,859 --> 00:11:34,902
[Mike chuckles]

176
00:11:34,985 --> 00:11:36,987
<i>Wimpy's? Let's go!</i>

177
00:11:37,071 --> 00:11:40,533
<i>I knew you noticed it!</i>
<i>All right, let's go!</i>

178
00:11:40,616 --> 00:11:43,369
<i>But you have</i>
<i>to promise you won't tell your mom.</i>

179
00:11:43,828 --> 00:11:47,289
<i>You know she doesn't</i>
<i>want you to eat before dinner.</i>

180
00:11:47,706 --> 00:11:50,209
<i>Just buy her an apple pie, Papa.</i>

181
00:11:50,292 --> 00:11:52,294
<i>- She'll forgive you!</i>
- [Mike laughs]

182
00:11:52,378 --> 00:11:55,714
<i>You said that, okay?</i>
<i>I'll tell this to her later.</i>

183
00:11:56,215 --> 00:11:57,174
<i>Let's go!</i>

184
00:12:00,010 --> 00:12:04,140
<i>Ah, Alice. When we get there,</i>
<i>I have something to ask you.</i>

185
00:12:04,682 --> 00:12:06,809
[Alice] He was
going to talk to me about…

186
00:12:07,560 --> 00:12:08,686
<i>Papa!</i>

187
00:12:08,769 --> 00:12:09,937
[truck horn honking]

188
00:12:10,479 --> 00:12:11,397
<i>Ah!</i>

189
00:12:11,814 --> 00:12:13,566
[Alice] But we got into an accident.

190
00:12:13,649 --> 00:12:17,570
[unsettling music playing]

191
00:12:17,653 --> 00:12:18,863
[metal clangs, thuds]

192
00:12:19,321 --> 00:12:20,281
He died!

193
00:12:20,364 --> 00:12:23,534
What happened to him
was payback for what the world did to me!

194
00:12:23,617 --> 00:12:25,161
[unsettling music continues]

195
00:12:25,244 --> 00:12:26,787
With everything this world took from me…

196
00:12:27,830 --> 00:12:28,789
Now.

197
00:12:30,291 --> 00:12:31,876
The world's making up to me.

198
00:12:34,795 --> 00:12:37,047
You disgusting pig!

199
00:12:37,131 --> 00:12:38,632
Papa died,

200
00:12:38,716 --> 00:12:41,802
carrying the weight of
what you had done to me!

201
00:12:41,886 --> 00:12:43,137
[sobbing]

202
00:12:44,054 --> 00:12:45,514
He trusted you.

203
00:12:46,265 --> 00:12:48,893
You… You weren't just his cousin.

204
00:12:48,976 --> 00:12:50,978
He treated you like his brother!

205
00:12:51,896 --> 00:12:53,147
And I…

206
00:12:53,898 --> 00:12:56,317
You were like my second father!

207
00:12:56,984 --> 00:12:59,612
- How could you do this to me?
- [ominous music playing]

208
00:12:59,695 --> 00:13:02,072
You're a monster! You're a monster!

209
00:13:02,156 --> 00:13:04,283
You're a monster! You're a monster!

210
00:13:04,366 --> 00:13:05,993
- Alice…
- You're a monster!

211
00:13:06,076 --> 00:13:08,496
You're a monster! You're a monster!

212
00:13:08,579 --> 00:13:10,289
- [Alice grunting]
- Alice!

213
00:13:11,999 --> 00:13:12,875
[anguished scream]

214
00:13:13,334 --> 00:13:14,668
You're a monster!

215
00:13:14,752 --> 00:13:18,547
- [breathing heavily, sobbing]
- [music fades]

216
00:13:22,343 --> 00:13:27,181
[unsettling music playing]

217
00:13:34,063 --> 00:13:35,397
Help!

218
00:13:35,481 --> 00:13:39,568
[grunting, muffled screaming]

219
00:13:40,486 --> 00:13:43,197
- Shh. Shh!
- [muffled scream]

220
00:13:43,280 --> 00:13:44,657
[music fades]

221
00:13:47,660 --> 00:13:50,120
Why hasn't Erica texted or called us yet?

222
00:13:50,704 --> 00:13:52,414
We should've received
an update by now, right?

223
00:13:53,082 --> 00:13:56,210
I don't know.
Alice should've been home by now, too.

224
00:13:56,293 --> 00:13:57,503
Where is she?

225
00:13:57,586 --> 00:13:58,963
At Uncle Edward's house.

226
00:14:00,506 --> 00:14:04,134
[foreboding music playing]

227
00:14:04,218 --> 00:14:05,970
She just suddenly collapsed.

228
00:14:06,053 --> 00:14:08,138
[officer] Let us take her to the hospital.

229
00:14:08,222 --> 00:14:09,223
[Edward] N-No need.

230
00:14:09,306 --> 00:14:10,683
Just stay here with my wife.

231
00:14:11,183 --> 00:14:13,435
I'll be more at peace if
someone's watching over her.

232
00:14:14,228 --> 00:14:16,438
We were tailing him,
but we lost him along the way.

233
00:14:16,522 --> 00:14:19,733
We went to their old house to check.
But he's not here either. How about you?

234
00:14:19,817 --> 00:14:21,277
[suspenseful music playing]

235
00:14:21,360 --> 00:14:23,112
The police lost him, too?

236
00:14:24,154 --> 00:14:25,239
Alright, thank you.

237
00:14:26,198 --> 00:14:28,576
Yes, he might've taken the back roads.

238
00:14:29,869 --> 00:14:32,162
Where else could
he have taken your father?

239
00:14:33,497 --> 00:14:36,625
[Edong] <i>It's not the police</i>
<i>who will make him pay.</i>

240
00:14:36,709 --> 00:14:38,711
<i>He killed our Mama.</i>

241
00:14:39,378 --> 00:14:43,382
<i>It is only right that</i>
<i>we deliver justice ourselves</i>…

242
00:14:44,133 --> 00:14:46,468
<i>When I meet Mama again,</i>

243
00:14:46,552 --> 00:14:48,804
<i>I want to tell her proudly</i>

244
00:14:48,888 --> 00:14:51,181
<i>that I have avenged her.</i>

245
00:14:53,017 --> 00:14:54,018
Mama!

246
00:14:54,727 --> 00:14:56,270
He must've taken Papa to Mama.

247
00:14:57,229 --> 00:14:58,856
[Crisanto grunting]

248
00:14:58,939 --> 00:15:00,024
Fuck you!

249
00:15:00,482 --> 00:15:03,027
- [grunts, groans]
- [kicks landing]

250
00:15:03,110 --> 00:15:06,196
[groaning, straining]

251
00:15:06,280 --> 00:15:11,452
[suspenseful music continues]

252
00:15:12,119 --> 00:15:15,664
[Crisanto groans, breathes heavily]

253
00:15:15,748 --> 00:15:17,124
[music fades]

254
00:15:19,293 --> 00:15:20,210
[Crisanto] Wait.

255
00:15:21,253 --> 00:15:23,172
What do you want, huh?

256
00:15:23,714 --> 00:15:25,424
For me to beg your mother?

257
00:15:25,883 --> 00:15:28,135
You want me to beg her?

258
00:15:29,386 --> 00:15:32,222
- [snickers]
- [foreboding music playing]

259
00:15:32,306 --> 00:15:34,391
I don't want anything from you.

260
00:15:40,314 --> 00:15:41,899
- [grunting]
- [body blow]

261
00:15:42,816 --> 00:15:44,109
- [groans]
- [thuds]

262
00:15:44,193 --> 00:15:48,238
[Edong snickers]

263
00:15:49,531 --> 00:15:52,076
Fuck you.

264
00:15:53,077 --> 00:15:55,287
Is that all you've got, huh?

265
00:15:56,497 --> 00:15:59,708
You can't even stand up.

266
00:15:59,792 --> 00:16:01,794
Yet you had the nerve to push me?

267
00:16:03,337 --> 00:16:08,842
[music becomes ominous]

268
00:16:08,926 --> 00:16:10,761
You're so pitiful.

269
00:16:12,137 --> 00:16:13,555
Fuck you!

270
00:16:13,973 --> 00:16:15,140
- [thwacks]
- [gun clatters]

271
00:16:16,058 --> 00:16:17,559
- [grunts]
- [body thuds]

272
00:16:17,643 --> 00:16:21,271
[coughing, groaning]

273
00:16:22,982 --> 00:16:24,149
[groans]

274
00:16:27,569 --> 00:16:29,113
- [groans]
- [flesh squelches]

275
00:16:29,196 --> 00:16:31,198
[screams in pain]

276
00:16:31,281 --> 00:16:33,283
[sobbing]

277
00:16:33,367 --> 00:16:35,411
[Crisanto] Fuck you!

278
00:16:37,037 --> 00:16:39,581
[wailing, sobbing]

279
00:16:39,665 --> 00:16:41,208
[grunting]

280
00:16:41,291 --> 00:16:43,002
[Crisanto] Fuck you!

281
00:16:43,085 --> 00:16:45,546
[grunting]

282
00:16:46,088 --> 00:16:48,090
- [Edong grunts]
- [groans]

283
00:16:51,343 --> 00:16:56,849
[Crisanto groaning]

284
00:16:56,932 --> 00:17:02,396
[Crisanto breathing heavily]

285
00:17:05,899 --> 00:17:10,112
[ominous music continues]

286
00:17:10,195 --> 00:17:13,866
I didn't bring you here for forgiveness.

287
00:17:16,035 --> 00:17:18,495
I brought you here to make you pay.

288
00:17:21,457 --> 00:17:26,086
I brought you here so I can give
Mama what I promised her long ago.

289
00:17:28,839 --> 00:17:30,215
Justice.

290
00:17:31,175 --> 00:17:34,636
Do you think your mother
will be happy about this, huh?

291
00:17:36,096 --> 00:17:37,097
How?

292
00:17:37,806 --> 00:17:39,725
You turned out just like me.

293
00:17:41,852 --> 00:17:43,062
You really are my son.

294
00:17:44,146 --> 00:17:46,398
A cunning murderer!

295
00:17:47,649 --> 00:17:50,069
I'm not like you.

296
00:17:51,195 --> 00:17:53,947
How many people have you killed, huh?

297
00:17:54,031 --> 00:17:55,616
[music becomes melancholic]

298
00:17:55,699 --> 00:17:57,785
And how many more are you going to kill?

299
00:17:58,911 --> 00:18:00,412
You killed women, right?

300
00:18:01,080 --> 00:18:02,331
Mothers, too!

301
00:18:04,291 --> 00:18:05,793
[grunting]

302
00:18:05,876 --> 00:18:07,377
[screams]

303
00:18:07,461 --> 00:18:09,505
[sobbing]

304
00:18:09,588 --> 00:18:13,634
[Edong grunting]

305
00:18:13,717 --> 00:18:16,470
[labored breathing]

306
00:18:21,892 --> 00:18:23,102
No.

307
00:18:24,269 --> 00:18:25,395
No.

308
00:18:26,063 --> 00:18:29,191
[sobs] I'm not like you!

309
00:18:30,859 --> 00:18:35,405
[melancholic music continues]

310
00:18:35,489 --> 00:18:37,366
I'm not your son.

311
00:18:38,492 --> 00:18:41,954
If your mother were still alive,

312
00:18:42,037 --> 00:18:44,373
she probably would've despised you

313
00:18:44,998 --> 00:18:48,127
because you've become just like me!

314
00:18:49,545 --> 00:18:51,255
Be quiet.

315
00:18:51,338 --> 00:18:52,506
[Crisanto] Or maybe…

316
00:18:53,465 --> 00:18:54,633
she would've left you,

317
00:18:55,259 --> 00:18:57,427
because she no longer wants to see

318
00:18:57,511 --> 00:18:59,429
your fucking face!

319
00:18:59,513 --> 00:19:02,432
Shut up!

320
00:19:02,516 --> 00:19:03,934
- [blow lands]
- [groans]

321
00:19:07,312 --> 00:19:09,439
[Crisanto snickers]

322
00:19:10,649 --> 00:19:12,693
If your mother were still alive right now,

323
00:19:14,194 --> 00:19:17,030
the two of us would've
beaten that fucking woman!

324
00:19:17,114 --> 00:19:18,073
- [grunts]
- [blow lands]

325
00:19:18,157 --> 00:19:19,074
[body thuds]

326
00:19:19,158 --> 00:19:25,664
- [Edong sobbing]
- [snickering]

327
00:19:27,541 --> 00:19:28,709
Edong.

328
00:19:29,168 --> 00:19:30,502
Think about it!

329
00:19:31,295 --> 00:19:32,963
- [gunshot]
- [music fades]

330
00:19:34,798 --> 00:19:38,677
[car engine revving]

331
00:19:40,512 --> 00:19:41,638
[groans]

332
00:19:50,063 --> 00:19:54,526
[engine continues revving]

333
00:20:00,073 --> 00:20:04,369
[tense music playing]

334
00:20:04,453 --> 00:20:05,704
[grunts]

335
00:20:05,787 --> 00:20:07,164
Alice. Alice!

336
00:20:07,247 --> 00:20:08,790
- Stop it!
- Alice, let go!

337
00:20:08,874 --> 00:20:10,417
I said let go! [grunting]

338
00:20:10,500 --> 00:20:11,501
[Alice grunts]

339
00:20:11,585 --> 00:20:13,253
- Alice!
- [tires screech]

340
00:20:13,337 --> 00:20:15,088
- Stop it!
- I said let go!

341
00:20:15,172 --> 00:20:18,175
- Alice! Alice! Alice!
- [tires screech]

342
00:20:18,258 --> 00:20:19,468
[engine revs]

343
00:20:19,551 --> 00:20:20,844
- [grunting]
- [Alice grunts]

344
00:20:21,637 --> 00:20:23,513
- [Edward screams]
- [thudding]

345
00:20:25,349 --> 00:20:26,725
[gunshot echoes]

346
00:20:27,559 --> 00:20:29,853
[crickets chirping]

347
00:20:30,854 --> 00:20:32,022
[body slumps]

348
00:20:33,815 --> 00:20:40,739
[somber music playing]

349
00:21:10,394 --> 00:21:11,395
[sniffles]

350
00:21:11,478 --> 00:21:13,730
What they're saying isn't true, Mama.

351
00:21:15,691 --> 00:21:17,567
[sobs] We're not the same.

352
00:21:20,112 --> 00:21:21,780
I'm not a monster

353
00:21:21,863 --> 00:21:24,032
like the person who killed you.

354
00:21:25,409 --> 00:21:26,994
I would never hurt you, Ma.

355
00:21:28,120 --> 00:21:30,080
I would never do that.

356
00:21:30,163 --> 00:21:34,584
[somber music continues]

357
00:21:34,668 --> 00:21:35,585
<i>Ma!</i>

358
00:21:37,212 --> 00:21:38,922
<i>Ma!</i>

359
00:21:42,926 --> 00:21:48,056
[sobs] <i>Ma!</i>

360
00:21:50,058 --> 00:21:52,019
What I'm doing right now…

361
00:21:53,312 --> 00:21:54,980
is necessary.

362
00:21:55,564 --> 00:21:57,190
And I'm the only one who can do it.

363
00:21:59,401 --> 00:22:04,448
I can't let them get away
with what they did to us, Ma.

364
00:22:06,033 --> 00:22:08,994
Everything they did to our family.

365
00:22:10,996 --> 00:22:12,748
I need to fulfill the reason

366
00:22:12,831 --> 00:22:14,666
why I was given another chance at life.

367
00:22:16,335 --> 00:22:17,961
You'll see, Ma.

368
00:22:18,837 --> 00:22:20,589
And you'll say…

369
00:22:22,924 --> 00:22:25,218
"My dear Edong was right."

370
00:22:29,347 --> 00:22:31,016
Go ahead and say it, Ma.

371
00:22:33,143 --> 00:22:34,728
Just this once.

372
00:22:38,732 --> 00:22:39,983
"My dear Edong."

373
00:22:40,067 --> 00:22:44,946
[somber music continues]

374
00:22:45,864 --> 00:22:50,202
[sobbing]

375
00:22:53,288 --> 00:22:54,873
[sniffles]

376
00:22:54,956 --> 00:22:59,169
[somber music continues]

377
00:23:09,638 --> 00:23:11,515
[music fades]

378
00:23:12,015 --> 00:23:13,850
Just watch me.

379
00:23:13,934 --> 00:23:17,604
[sinister music playing]

380
00:23:18,105 --> 00:23:20,065
[Alice grunts, sobs]

381
00:23:21,316 --> 00:23:25,320
[sighs heavily, coughing]

382
00:23:28,657 --> 00:23:30,242
[gasping, breathing shakily]

383
00:23:30,325 --> 00:23:33,036
[unsettling music playing]

384
00:23:33,120 --> 00:23:35,956
[Edward coughing, groans]

385
00:23:36,039 --> 00:23:40,710
- [Alice breathing rapidly]
- [groaning]

386
00:23:40,794 --> 00:23:43,046
[tense music playing]

387
00:23:43,130 --> 00:23:44,256
What are you doing?

388
00:23:44,840 --> 00:23:46,466
Where do you think you're going?

389
00:23:46,550 --> 00:23:48,677
- Just stay here!
- [Alice whimpers]

390
00:23:48,760 --> 00:23:50,470
Stay here, Alice!

391
00:23:53,140 --> 00:23:53,974
Alice!

392
00:23:54,057 --> 00:23:55,809
- [grunts]
- [screams in pain]

393
00:23:58,145 --> 00:23:59,187
[blow lands]

394
00:23:59,729 --> 00:24:01,940
[Edward] Alice! Alice!

395
00:24:02,440 --> 00:24:03,650
[grunting]

396
00:24:03,733 --> 00:24:05,152
[Edward] Alice!

397
00:24:05,235 --> 00:24:07,195
Fuck you!

398
00:24:07,279 --> 00:24:08,363
Alice!

399
00:24:08,446 --> 00:24:09,781
- [Alice breathing heavily]
- [music ends]

400
00:24:09,865 --> 00:24:11,032
[Erica] Are you serious?

401
00:24:11,116 --> 00:24:12,159
He's there?

402
00:24:13,451 --> 00:24:14,703
Alright, thank you.

403
00:24:15,704 --> 00:24:17,038
You were right.

404
00:24:17,122 --> 00:24:19,291
Edong took Crisanto to your mother.

405
00:24:19,374 --> 00:24:21,710
Locsin said
they spotted the van at the cemetery.

406
00:24:21,793 --> 00:24:23,211
They're on their way there.

407
00:24:23,295 --> 00:24:26,840
[phone buzzing]

408
00:24:28,967 --> 00:24:29,926
Hello, Beth?

409
00:24:30,719 --> 00:24:32,345
The police have located Edong.

410
00:24:32,429 --> 00:24:34,181
[Erica] <i>We're on our way to the cemetery.</i>

411
00:24:34,764 --> 00:24:36,474
[Beth] I'm on my way to the hospital.

412
00:24:36,892 --> 00:24:39,936
I heard Uncle Edward took Alice
to the hospital after she collapsed.

413
00:24:40,437 --> 00:24:42,272
What? Why? What happened?

414
00:24:42,355 --> 00:24:44,733
Alice went to visit Uncle Edward.

415
00:24:44,816 --> 00:24:46,193
She stayed there for a while.

416
00:24:46,276 --> 00:24:48,862
<i>When we tried to contact her,</i>
<i>she couldn't be reached.</i>

417
00:24:49,237 --> 00:24:52,407
So, I went there myself.
And the police told me she collapsed.

418
00:24:52,908 --> 00:24:55,160
Mel and I will meet at the hospital.

419
00:24:55,243 --> 00:24:57,495
Have you talked to Uncle Edward?

420
00:24:57,579 --> 00:24:59,372
Tsk. He couldn't be reached either.

421
00:25:00,207 --> 00:25:02,375
Hopefully, nothing bad happens to Alice.

422
00:25:05,754 --> 00:25:07,547
[foreboding music playing]

423
00:25:07,631 --> 00:25:08,590
[Beth] Erica.

424
00:25:09,007 --> 00:25:10,050
Erica, wait.

425
00:25:11,009 --> 00:25:12,302
Hello? Beth.

426
00:25:13,553 --> 00:25:15,096
It's Uncle Edward's van…

427
00:25:16,181 --> 00:25:17,599
It crashed.

428
00:25:17,682 --> 00:25:19,309
Looks like they got into an accident.

429
00:25:19,392 --> 00:25:21,102
[foreboding music continues]

430
00:25:21,186 --> 00:25:23,104
[tires screech]

431
00:25:23,188 --> 00:25:25,315
Beth. Hello? Beth!

432
00:25:26,066 --> 00:25:27,192
Hello, Erica.

433
00:25:27,817 --> 00:25:28,735
Alice?!

434
00:25:29,653 --> 00:25:30,779
Uncle!

435
00:25:31,238 --> 00:25:32,489
Beth, what's going on?

436
00:25:34,157 --> 00:25:39,246
[foreboding music continues]

437
00:25:39,329 --> 00:25:40,914
Erica, they're not here.

438
00:25:40,997 --> 00:25:41,957
Huh?

439
00:25:42,332 --> 00:25:43,833
What do you mean?

440
00:25:43,917 --> 00:25:46,211
[Beth] <i>I'm at the van,</i>
<i>but they're not here.</i>

441
00:25:46,670 --> 00:25:48,797
I-- I'm on Dalanginan Road.

442
00:25:50,131 --> 00:25:51,716
<i>Louisa, where are you?</i>

443
00:25:52,259 --> 00:25:53,343
<i>Louisa?</i>

444
00:25:53,426 --> 00:25:55,470
I'll call an ambulance
and tell them to go there.

445
00:25:55,553 --> 00:25:57,389
I'll look for Alice.

446
00:25:57,472 --> 00:25:59,557
Uncle Edward and
Alice got into an accident.

447
00:25:59,641 --> 00:26:02,102
Beth saw the van, but they weren't there.

448
00:26:02,185 --> 00:26:03,311
I have to go to them.

449
00:26:03,395 --> 00:26:04,646
What about my brother?

450
00:26:04,729 --> 00:26:07,565
Marco and the police are
on their way to the cemetery.

451
00:26:07,649 --> 00:26:08,900
You don't have to come with me,

452
00:26:08,984 --> 00:26:10,819
but you have to drop
me off at Beth's location.

453
00:26:12,279 --> 00:26:14,364
[phone ringing]

454
00:26:14,447 --> 00:26:15,323
Hello, Mel?

455
00:26:15,407 --> 00:26:17,200
Beth, I'm on my way to the hospital.

456
00:26:17,284 --> 00:26:19,244
[Beth] <i>I'm on Dalanginan Road.</i>

457
00:26:19,744 --> 00:26:20,537
What?

458
00:26:20,620 --> 00:26:23,540
Uncle Edward's van is here.
They got into an accident.

459
00:26:23,623 --> 00:26:25,625
But they're no longer in the van.

460
00:26:26,334 --> 00:26:27,585
Does it look bad?

461
00:26:27,669 --> 00:26:28,962
I don't know.

462
00:26:29,504 --> 00:26:31,339
[Mel] <i>Maybe someone already helped them.</i>

463
00:26:31,423 --> 00:26:33,174
I'll check the hospital, okay?

464
00:26:33,258 --> 00:26:34,843
You're almost there, right?

465
00:26:34,926 --> 00:26:36,720
Can you check if they're already there?

466
00:26:36,803 --> 00:26:39,472
Yeah. I'll call you right away, okay?

467
00:26:39,556 --> 00:26:40,724
Okay, okay.

468
00:26:43,351 --> 00:26:44,477
Alice?

469
00:26:51,026 --> 00:26:56,948
[foreboding music intensifies]

470
00:26:57,032 --> 00:26:58,074
Alice!

471
00:27:04,873 --> 00:27:06,416
- Alice!
- [music crescendos]

472
00:27:08,126 --> 00:27:09,502
[whimpers]

473
00:27:09,586 --> 00:27:10,545
- [Edward] <i>Alice?</i>
- [Alice] <i>Help!</i>

474
00:27:10,628 --> 00:27:12,380
<i>Let's treat your wound.</i>

475
00:27:12,464 --> 00:27:14,591
<i>If we don't, you might bleed to death.</i>

476
00:27:14,674 --> 00:27:15,967
<i>Alice, where are you?</i>

477
00:27:16,051 --> 00:27:17,510
[Mel] <i>Beth… Beth, I can't.</i>

478
00:27:17,594 --> 00:27:19,471
<i>This is just like that night.</i>

479
00:27:19,554 --> 00:27:21,806
<i>- Louisa?</i>
<i>- Help!</i>

480
00:27:21,890 --> 00:27:23,683
<i>The night Louisa was killed.</i>

481
00:27:23,767 --> 00:27:25,185
[Louisa] <i>Help! Aah!</i>

482
00:27:25,268 --> 00:27:26,311
<i>- Come here!</i>
- [grunts]

483
00:27:26,394 --> 00:27:28,855
<i>No, this is different.</i>
<i>They're not the same.</i>

484
00:27:28,938 --> 00:27:30,065
<i>I'm sorry, Alice.</i>

485
00:27:30,148 --> 00:27:32,442
- [Alice gasps]
<i>- It breaks my heart to do this.</i>

486
00:27:32,525 --> 00:27:33,777
[screams]

487
00:27:34,319 --> 00:27:35,320
<i>No!</i>

488
00:27:35,403 --> 00:27:37,322
- [Mel] <i>No!</i>
- [grunting]
